  "response": "The best time to visit Kerala is from September to March, which is the post-monsoon and winter season. Here's a suggested 8-day itinerary covering key destinations:\n\nBest Season:\n- September to March (Pleasant weather, minimal rainfall)\n- Temperature ranges from 18\u00b0C to 30\u00b0C\n- Ideal for sightseeing and outdoor activities\n\n8-Day Kerala Itinerary:\n\nDay 1-2: Kochi\n- Fort Kochi\n- Chinese Fishing Nets\n- Jewish Synagogue\n- Mattancherry Palace\n- Jew Town\n- Art galleries and cafes\n\nDay 3-4: Munnar\n- Tea plantations\n- Eravikulam National Park\n- Tea Museum\n- Echo Point\n- Mattupetty Dam\n- Top Station\n\nDay 5-6: Alleppey\n- Houseboat cruise in backwaters\n- Village walks\n- Paddy field views\n- Authentic Kerala cuisine\n- Sunset views\n\nDay 7-8: Thekkady\n- Periyar Wildlife Sanctuary\n- Spice plantations\n- Boat safari\n- Tribal village tours\n- Elephant interactions\n\nTravel Tips:\n- Book accommodations in advance\n- Carry light, comfortable clothing\n- Try local cuisine\n- Respect local customs",
